Q: What has been your greatest challenge? 
A: Good question. My greatest challenge has been letting go of something I assumed would always be a part of me in the same way. Most difficult was the time that led up to receiving the rite of passage. Trying to imagine how a different existence would feel was overwhelming. Salty tears flooded me for a while. I was more. I had bloomed in the face of adversity.
